						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Chōḻa, Paranthaka I, Year 30 = 937 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The King's name is engraved over an erasure. Gift of gold (30 <hi rend="italic">pon</hi>) for offerings atnoon and for a lamp in the temple of Tiruvānaikal Perumānaḍigaḷ at Tiruveḷḷaṟai. The donor was Kuvāvaṉ Chēndi wife of Chāttuvāy Chēndan Mādēvaṉ, who belonged to the same village. She gave another 40 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of <hi rend="italic">pon</hi> for the village tank.</p>						

						</summary>
